        <h2>Introduction</h2>

        <h3>Definition and Classification of Drugs</h3>
        <p>
          Drugs are substances that alter the physical or mental functioning of
          the body. They can be legal, such as alcohol, or illegal, like heroin.
          They are also classified based on their effects: stimulants (such as
          caffeine), depressants (such as alcohol), and hallucinogens (such as
          LSD). Drug use may stem from curiosity, peer pressure, pain relief, or
          the desire to enhance performance. Historically, many drugs have been
          used for medicinal or recreational purposes, which has influenced how
          they are regulated.
        </p>

