        <h3>History of Drug Use in Different Cultures</h3>
        <p>
          Drugs have been part of various cultures for centuries. In Greece,
          opium was used for medical and religious purposes; in South America,
          coca leaves were chewed to reduce hunger. In Mesoamerica, mushrooms
          and peyote were used in rituals, and in India, cannabis had spiritual
          uses. Over time, many substances were synthesized, regulated, and
          debated for their effects and legality.
        </p>
