        <h3>Psychological Aspects</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>Addiction and Dependence</strong>: Addiction is a chronic
          brain disorder characterized by the compulsive seeking of drugs and
          continued use despite negative consequences. It develops due to
          changes in the brain's reward system, which reinforces drug-seeking
          behavior. Dependence can be physical or psychological. Physical
          dependence occurs when the body adapts to the substance and develops
          withdrawal symptoms if its use is discontinued. Psychological
          dependence involves intense cravings and a subjective need to use the
          drug to cope with emotional or social situations.
        </p>

        <div class="section-image">
