        <p>
          <strong>Psychological Impact of Drug Use</strong>: Prolonged drug use
          can severely affect mental health. Some drugs can trigger or worsen
          disorders such as anxiety, depression, and schizophrenia. Opioids can
          cause emotional numbness and cognitive impairment. Stimulants can
          induce psychotic episodes and paranoia. In some cases, the abuse of
          hallucinogens can lead to dissociative disorders and persistent
          alterations in perception.
        </p>

