        <h3>Public Health</h3>
        <p>
          Drug use is a big problem in many countries. It affects public health
          and the environment. People use drugs for different reasons. Young
          people, especially in cities and poor areas, use drugs more. Men use
          more drugs, but women can have more health problems.
        </p>
        <p>
          Drug use causes more emergencies, hospital visits, and the need for
          special treatment. It also affects jobs, education, and increases
          crime. This costs a lot of money for health systems and governments.
        </p>
        <p>
          Injecting drugs is dangerous because people sometimes share dirty
          needles. This spreads diseases like HIV and hepatitis C. Drug use can
          also lead to risky actions, like unsafe sex, which spreads other
          diseases. Some countries help by giving clean needles and medicine
          like methadone to reduce harm.
        </p>

