        <h3>Drugs and the Environment</h3>
        <p>
          Drugs also hurt nature. People use strong chemicals to make drugs.
          These chemicals go into the water and the ground and kill plants and
          animals. The pollution can also affect people who live nearby.
        </p>
        <p>
          Drug traffickers sometimes use illegal mining to get money. This
          mining destroys the land, pollutes with mercury, and changes rivers.
        </p>
        <p>
          To grow more coca or poppy, traffickers cut down forests and use toxic
          pesticides. This kills other plants, animals, and makes the soil bad.
          It also adds to climate change.
        </p>
        <p>
          Sometimes governments destroy drug crops using airplanes and chemicals
          like glyphosate. But this can also damage good crops and make people
          sick.
        </p>

