        <h3>Ethical Perspectives</h3>

        <h5>Ethical Debates</h5>
        <p>
          Drug use raises complex ethical dilemmas, particularly at the
          intersection of individual freedom and public health. While some argue
          that individuals have the right to consume psychoactive substances as
          long as they do not harm others, others contend that the state must
          intervene to prevent social and health-related harms.
        </p>

        <h5>State Control vs. Personal Freedom</h5>
        <p>
          The role of the state in regulating drug use is a topic of ongoing
          debate. While some countries have opted for tolerance and harm
          reduction policies, others maintain strict punitive approaches.The
          legalization of cannabis in various parts of the world has opened the
          discussion about the possibility of regulating other substances, under
          the argument that proper regulation can reduce the risks associated
          with the black market and generate tax revenue for health programs.
        </p>

